(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Dubai &mdash; Qatar says hackers broke into the website of its state-run news agency and published a fake story quoting the country's ruling Emir.The hack happened early on Wednesday morning and the website of the Qatar News Agency wasn't immediately accessible.The fake article claimed the small, gas-rich nation had ordered its ambassadors from Bahrain, Egypt, Kuwait, Saudi Arabia and United Arab Emirates withdrawn over "tension" with the administration of US President Donald Trump. The fake article also quoted Qatar Emir Sheikh Tamim bin Hamad Al Thani calling Iran an "Islamic power" and saying Qatar's relations with Israel were "good".A statement from Sheikh Saif Bin Ahmed Al Thani, the director of the Qatar's government communications office, said an investigation was ongoing. He said Qatar "will hold all those committed accountable". 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.